metadata.name: Kinetograms #85
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: a manifested realization #66
metadata.description:
In general, this piece continues my study of procedural abstract expressionism. However, I've developed a new small bit of code I am testing here; I am trying to create a "clumping" noise function that looks natural but doesn't have the obvious "look" of Perlin noise, and is more controllable. This piece contains my first public use of this. So it is, in a way, a test. 

I was inspired by the IRL paintings of Francesco D'Adamo, specifically his "Manifesti" series, although (as is the way of things) the end result looks nothing like what I started with, and is a more general 1950s abstract expressionism look. 

This piece is a gift to the collectors of all my recent "a" mints. Thank you all!

metadata.name: FRAG || DEFRAG #17
metadata.description:
FRAG || DEFRAG is structured from the superposition of simple shapes, such as triangles, that alternate in different layers and blending modes. In this scenario, visual complexity is revealed at different times and intensities, offering countless possibilities of perception.

Along with this, the chromatic variation with unique gradations associated with the play of lights and shadows, gives the project different perspectives and depths, in continuous and complementary cycles of fragmentation and defragmentation.

Thus, as in everything that surrounds us, the resulting form does not end in itself, but presents itself as a result of the combination of several other distinct elements.

Nothing is just one thing.

#Main Features
- 13 color schemes “zones”:

* Shadow Sky and Bronze – 12,5% chance
* TIF, Soldier, Zreen and Ice – 10% chance each
* Vascai – 7,5% chance
* Burn Golden, Gray, Lemonade, REC and BR – 5% chance 
* 80’s – 2,5% chance

- 3 canvas formats;
- 3 frequency;
- 2 gradient type;
- 3 degrees of granulometry;

- 1 ultrarare feature | negative effect 

There is only a 1% chance of the negative effect appearing, if you are lucky you will see the following message. "YOU WIN A FREE EDITION OF MY NEXT PROJECT"

Obs.: 
- The first 5 iterations will entitle you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The rendering process should take a few seconds, so enjoy the look of the triangles in action.

July 30, 2022

Generative Token by Morbeck for fxhash.

metadata.name: a manifested realization #16
metadata.description:

This piece contains my first public use of this. So it is, in a way, a test.

This piece is a gift to the collectors of all my recent "a" mints. Thank you all!

metadata.name: [glitchscape] #125
metadata.description:
this glitchy landscape is a place for you to get lost in as you wander keep your hands in your pockets keep your soul close don't stare at the sun it is oh so hungry.  

enjoy the evening sky.

---

this piece progressively renders until the final result is in place. please be patient as it chunks along depositing pixels to the screen.

palettes via chromotome.

---

press 's' to save high-res (3000x3000) image at any step of the way.
